    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen running `--embed` with `--listen` neovim will exit if it can't open a channel over stdio. Discussed in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/29634#issuecomment-4114177186, and looking over the code, it looks like that's not fully intentional?\n\nHere's where embed + listen are considered\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/929f03fa8c6263044496b7c92af4058ac1c28ced/src/nvim/main.c#L442\n\nand the implementation of `remote_ui_wait_for_attach` seems to do the right thing:\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/929f03fa8c6263044496b7c92af4058ac1c28ced/src/nvim/api/ui.c#L122-L140\n\nbut before all that there's a check for embedded mode, and it exits if neovim cannot make a channel from stdio regardless if `--listen` is set\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/929f03fa8c6263044496b7c92af4058ac1c28ced/src/nvim/main.c#L322-L327\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\nssh HOST 'nvim -u NONE --embed --listen 0.0.0.0:8888 &'\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`nvim` would keep waiting until a UI connects.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.6\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
